Network Technology

5G

5 min read Glossary
Quick Definition

5G is the fifth generation of mobile network technology that delivers significantly faster data speeds, lower latency, and improved network capacity compared to 4G LTE. It uses advanced antenna technology and new radio frequencies to enable download speeds up to 10-100 times faster than previous generations.

Deep Dive

How This Applies to Vouch Mobile

Vouch Mobile includes full 5G access at no additional cost with every plan. Our service runs on AT&T's nationwide 5G network, giving you access to one of the largest and fastest 5G networks in the country. Whether you're streaming 4K video, downloading large files, or gaming online, you'll automatically connect to 5G wherever it's available and enjoy the improved speeds and lower latency.
